<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Calling OS_GenericSymbolLookup_Impl with SymbolName that is not guaranteed to be a valid NUL-terminated character string can cause the underlying dlsym implementation to use string handling routines (e.g. strlen/strcmp) and read past the end of the object. The code only checks the pointer for NULL (OS_CHECK_POINTER) but does not ensure the buffer is NUL-terminated or within bounds, so passing an unterminated or truncated buffer can lead to out-of-bounds accesses of objects referenced by pointer parameters to string.h functions.
</scenario>
